`crates/ctx-summarize` is a Cargo crate root: `src/` implements the
bottom-up `.ctx` summarizer (CLI + orchestration over `Fs`/`Agent`
traits), and `tests/` is the integration suite pinning that runner's
external contract (ordering, error variants, scope boundaries) against
fakes and real subprocesses. A caller building or modifying this crate
should treat the two subtrees as tightly coupled: any change to
`runner::run`'s ordering, `SummError` variants, or `MAX_TARGETS`/access
gating in `src/` must be matched by an updated assertion in
`tests/summarize.rs`, and vice versa — the test file is effectively the
executable spec for `src/runner.rs`.

The crate has no top-level `intent.md`; behavior is documented only
through the two subtree rollups. `src/`'s prompt-file and `.context`
mirror conventions (`cpath.rs`, `summarizer-*.md`) are exercised, not
redefined, by the tests — fixture prompts and paths in `tests/` must stay
consistent with what `runner::load_prompts`/`cpath` actually expect.
`SubprocessAgent` integration tests additionally require `sh`, `cat`,
`true`, `exit` on PATH, an environment dependency outside the crate's own
control.

intent_divergence: no intent.md exists at this directory or either
subtree, so no stated intent can be checked against this description.